-- FACTBOX: The 10 best-liked companies in the United States
-- 
-- Mon Jun 23, 2008 1:20am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/23/us-usa-corporate-reputation-factbox-idUSN2237069220080623

 

 (Reuters) - Google Inc now has the best reputation in corporate America, according to a poll by Harris Interactive released on Monday. 

 The Web search company displaced Microsoft Corp in the No. 1 spot, while the maker of Windows software fell to 10th place. Chipmaker Intel Corp, food company Kraft -- which hadn't even factored into the top 60 last year -- Warren Buffett's investment company Berkshire Hathaway Inc and Japanese automaker Honda Motor Co all found their way into the top 10, the Harris Interactive Reputation Quotient survey found. Below is a list of the top 10 best-known U.S. companies by reputation, followed by their rank in last year's survey: 1. Google 4 2. Johnson & Johnson 2 3. Intel 16 4. General Mills Inc 6 5. Kraft Foods Inc not listed 6. Berkshire Hathaway 21 7. 3M Co 3 8. Coca-Cola Co 5 9. Honda 14 10. Microsoft 1